'''''lumbulë''''' (or ''lumbule'') is a [[Quenya]] word meaning "(heavy) shadow; dark shadow".<ref>{{FR|II8}} (form: ''lumbulë'')</ref><ref>{{HM|RGEO}}, "[[Namárië]]" (HarperCollins 2002; pp. 23, 67; form: ''lumbule'')</ref><ref name=PE17>{{PE|17}}, p. 72 (form: ''lumbule'')</ref>

==Etymology==
The word seems to be an extended/augmentative form of the word ''[[lumbe]]'' "gloom" (cf. ''[[tumba]]'' and ''[[tumbale]]''), from [[Sundocarme|root]] [[LUM]].<ref>{{LR|Etymologies}}, p. 370</ref>

==Examples==
{{quote|[[ar]] [[ilya|ilyë]] [[tie]]r [[undulav-|undulávë]] '''lumbulë'''; ('and all paths are drowned deep in '''shadow''';')|''[[Namárië]]''}}

==Other versions==

In the ''Qenya Lexicon'' appears the [[Qenya]] word ''lumbo'' ("dark lowering cloud").<ref>{{PE|12}}</ref>

